Percy Tau says he will stay at Brighton next season! This is despite him spending most of the time on the bench with the English Premier League side. Tau is in the country where he was handover a Hyundai i30 at the dealership's Headquarters on Wednesday. "I was happy to have contributed to the team in those few games that I've  played," he said. "It  has been six months since I arrived there, and if they want to loan me out they will do that based on what? "I didn't play enough. I will continue to fight for my position next season because I always see a future there. "I will stay that's my position right now." 